<dl id="n12189e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12189e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12189e"> 189(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ allodial ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Alongside it, on the continent at any rate, were survivals, if not of Roman ownership, at any rate of that German system of absolute ownership known to mediaeval lawyers as &ldquo;<mark>allodial</mark>,&rdquo; a system which never completely died out up to the French Revolution, and which may now be said to be the base on which the possession of landed property rests in Western Europe. <small> W.F. Butler, &ldquo;Irish Land Tenures&rdquo; <a name="IRLT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IRLT"><cite title="source">Studies</cite></a> (June 1924) 294-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
